  <!-- ================================================================
       CATEGORY K: AWS SDK v1 and ion-java — transitives via X-Ray SDK
       ================================================================
       aws-xray-recorder-sdk-core 2.x internally depends on AWS SDK v1
       (aws-java-sdk-core), which brings in ion-java and jmespath-java.
       These jars are not used directly by application code; they exist
       only to support X-Ray tracing calls to the AWS X-Ray API.
       ion-java parses only AWS X-Ray service responses (trusted AWS
       infrastructure), so attacker-controlled deeply-nested Ion data
       (the CVE-2024-21634 vector) cannot reach it in our deployment.
       Re-evaluate when X-Ray SDK drops its AWS SDK v1 dependency.
  -->
  <suppress>
    <notes>ion-java is a transitive of aws-java-sdk-core (X-Ray); only parses trusted AWS service responses. Re-evaluate when X-Ray SDK drops SDK v1.</notes>
    <gav regex="true">^software\.amazon\.ion:ion-java:.*$</gav>
    <cve>CVE-2024-21634</cve>
  </suppress>
  <suppress>
    <notes>aws-java-sdk-core v1 is a transitive of aws-xray-recorder-sdk-core; not used directly. Re-evaluate when X-Ray SDK drops SDK v1.</notes>
    <gav regex="true">^com\.amazonaws:aws-java-sdk-core:.*$</gav>
    <cve>CVE-2022-31159</cve>
  </suppress>
  <suppress>
    <notes>aws-java-sdk-xray v1 is a transitive of aws-xray-recorder-sdk-core; not used directly. Re-evaluate when X-Ray SDK drops SDK v1.</notes>
    <gav regex="true">^com\.amazonaws:aws-java-sdk-xray:.*$</gav>
    <cve>CVE-2022-31159</cve>
  </suppress>
  <suppress>
    <notes>jmespath-java v1 is a transitive of aws-java-sdk-core; not used directly. Re-evaluate when X-Ray SDK drops SDK v1.</notes>
    <gav regex="true">^com\.amazonaws:jmespath-java:.*$</gav>
    <cve>CVE-2022-31159</cve>
  </suppress>

